Images were acquired on a 4K charge-coupled device cam - era (Eagle; FEI) at 84270× (1.78 Å/pixel) using the TOM_acquisition  package (Korinek et al., 2011; available at http://www.biochem.mpg   .de/baumeister/tom_e/get_tom/index.html).
TOM_tool_box programs re - quire MATLAB, a commercially available software package (for informa - tion see http://www.mathworks.com).

Particles were selected from micrographs automatically by cross corre - lation (CC) with a reference using scripts (see online supplemental material)  written for the SPIDER package (Shaikh et al., 2008; SPIDER is open software  freely available with excellent documentation, tutorials and sample scripts at  http://www.wadsworth.org/spider_doc/spider/docs/spider.html).
Analysis of spectra was   performed with the MASCOT software (Matrix Science) on the complete  N. crassa  genome database (http://www.broad.mit.edu/annotation/fungi/ neurospora).

The results of HHpred were then used to generate a molecular  homology model for Tob55 based on the FhaC structure using MODELLER  (Sali et al., 1995); both programs are accessible for use online through the  Bioinformatics toolkit, Gene Center, Ludwig Maximilians University Munich  (http://toolkit.lmb.uni-muenchen.de).
